Vheadline
p2
VYoung and promising singers make their mark
p3
sVnews
p4
VYoung Modumudi Sruti Ranjani is a talented vocalist showing abundant promise. She is the daughter and the disciple of musicians &#8212; Modumudi Sudhakar and Aanjana Sudhakar. Trained well by her parents, Sruti began her musical career at the age of eight. Sudhakar is a reputed vidwan and senior composer in Vijayawada Akashvani. Sruti is trained in light, devotional and classical music and also lent her voice for a couple of movies to be released soon.This year she bagged the Akashvani National competitions in the light music category. Sruti Ranjani received many awards and accolades in several prestigious competitions in the State. In ETV's popular programme hosted by S.P. Balasubramanyam, Srutiranjani she was selected as &#8216;Voice of the District'. She will be receiving the Akashvani National award on February 24.Tatha Swathi Ramya is another talented teenager. This school-going singer gave a concert of Annamacharya keertanas organised by Sri Annamayya Sankeertana gana Prachara Bhakta Brindam, established by vocal vidwan Pappu Sadasiva Sastri. The concert took place at Sri Sringeri Peetha Paripalita Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram, Vijayawada.A disciple of Suseela Gopalam, Modumudi Sudhakar and Anjana Sudhakar, Swati Ramya began singing from the age of seven and received many awards from various competitions. Technical finery, neat diction and bhava sense marked her singing. In her concert Swati Ramya rendered a large number of Annamayya keertanas some of the highlights being Anjaneya Anilaja (Arabhi), Namo Narayanaya (Sriragam), Vedamula (Madhyamavathi), Amaregada Nedu (Devagandhari) and Koluvaiyunnadu (Kalyani).
